@0 = ~Ach!, The ichor on this damned blade nearly burned right through me glove!  Be this sword from the hells themselves?~
@1 = ~Ye know, I might be able to improve it with a blazing sword as fiery as the hells themselves and a scroll of disintegrate to reduce it to its essence.  Or I could use a Githyanki's silver hilt if'n ye could wrestle one away from the beasts.~
@2 = ~Let's see if ye got what I need to reforge that hellish blade of yours...~
@3 = ~Well, let's see what else ye got.~
@4 = ~Ah, the hellblade again eh?  Last time this damnable blade nearly ruined my best hammer!~
@5 = ~It be a tall order to improve this blade further, I'd need an elemental gemstone of ichor, along with 15,000gp for the work.~
@6 = ~This be the gemstone we need, I can improve that hellish blade with it if'n ye want.~
@7 = ~What's this? A right nice pair of boots these are, quite soft and quiet.~
@8 = ~I could improve these boots with some liquid mercury and a commission of 7500gp.~
@9 = ~Ah, thats some liquid mercury alright, I can improve these boots with them.~
@10 = ~What've ye got here?  Hah! a crown of false gemstones and gold.  Still, it seems to have a bit o' enchantment to it.~
@11 = ~I could make this false crown ring true with real gemstones of emerald, diamond, star sapphire, a potion of insight and 5,000gp.~
@12 = ~This looks to be the gems I need, and the potion.  I can reforge that crown of yours into one fit for a king if ye'd like.~
@13 = ~Blessed be!  A fine dwarven helm bearing the mark of Dumathoin!~
@14 = ~All I would need are some good horns, and 5,000gp and I can make the glory of Dumathoin really shine from this helm.~
@15 = ~These horns will do nicely, I can use these to make that dwarven helm of yours into something Dumathoin himself would be proud to wear.~
@16 = ~Hmm, an amulet made of petrified eyes?  Cannae say I've ever seen anything of the like.~
@17 = ~I might be able to make these old eyes see further with a scroll of farsight, wizard eye, a couple of potions of perception, and 5,000gp.~
@18 = ~Here we are, the scrolls and potions I need to enhanced those blind eyes on your amulet.~
@19 = ~This be a nice belt o' skill you have here, Keenedge's work if'n I'm not mistaken.~
@20 = ~Ol' Cromwell can make this belt even better for ye, I just need some gauntlets of weapon skill and expertise along with a scroll of distintegrate to transfer the magics and 10,000gp for the work.~
@21 = ~Ye got the gauntlets and scroll, I can get to work on improving Sa'yan's belt for ye if'n ye want.~
@22 = ~Nice sharp throwing dart ye have here, I almost pricked me fingers on it.~
@23 = ~I can improve this bloody dart of yours with five scrolls of melf's acid arrow, five sphene gems, and 5,000gp.~
@24 = ~Lemme see, ye got the five scrolls and sphene gems, I can get right to work on that dart for ya if'n ye want.~
@25 = ~Bloody hells!  Just touching this blade's hilt makes me feel as weak as a young lass!~
@26 = ~I cannae enhance this blade unless ye finds me a skull of dark power, mayhap a lich's.  And I would need 15,000gp for me trouble.~
@27 = ~I'll be a basilisk's lunch, that be a dark skull from a lich alright.  I can use it to enhance that black blade of yours.~
@28 = ~Bloody hells!  Just touching this hammer's haft makes me feel as weak as a young lass!~
@29 = ~I cannae enhance this hammer unless ye finds me a skull of dark power, mayhap a lich's.  And I would need 15,000gp for me trouble.~
@30 = ~I'll be a basilisk's lunch, that be a dark skull from a lich alright.  I can use it to enhance that black hammer of yours.~
@31 = ~What's this 'ere?  Some spoony bard's hat?~
@32 = ~I can make this pretentious hat more practical for a minstrel with ioun stones of gold and dusty rose.  Toss in 7,500gp for the day's work and Cromwell will do ye right.~
@33 = ~Aye, ioun stones of both gold and dusty rose ye have here, I can get to work on that musician's hat o' yours if ye would like.~
@34 = ~What've ye got there, a Thayvian mage's robe?~
@35 = ~If'n ye happen to come across the robe of vecna, I can use its threading and magics to enhance that flamin' conjurer's robe of yours.  It would cost ye 10,000gp for the commission.~
@36 = ~I see ye've managed to get the old lich's robe, quite impressive.  I can use it to improve that Thayvian robe if'n ye want.~
@37 = ~What's this now?  One of the bucklers from those mercenaries at Baldur's Gate?~
@38 = ~This old dwarf can rework that Flaming Fist buckler of yours into something special if'n ye can provide me with a reflection shield +1, two scrolls of protection against normal missiles, two potions of mirrored eyes, and 10,000gp for me trouble.~
@39 = ~Ye've got the reflection shield, scrolls, and potions.  I can rework that Flaming Fist buckler of yours if'n ye would like.~
@40 = ~Is this?.... Hah!  It is!  The false "Crom Faeyr".  Where in the realms did you find this accursed thing?~
@41 = ~Hmmm, I might be able to improve that accursed hammer if'n you can find me a rune of clangeddin to scribe into it.  It would take 5,000gp fer the work.~
@42 = ~This be one of the clangeddin runes alright, I can use it to enhance that blasphemous hammer of yours.~
@43 = ~What've ye here?  The balance and heft of this burning blade be all wrong, was it even made to be held by mortal hands?~
@44 = ~I can reforge that unbalanced flamin' blade of yours, and make it a far more effective and balanced weapon.  I would just need a sword of flame, a blade of searing, and five scrolls of agannazar's scorcher.  7,500gp for the day's work at the forge and it'd be a done deal for ye.~
@45 = ~A flaming sword, a searing blade, and five of the scorcher scrolls.  I can get right to work on reforging that unweildy burning sword of yours if ye'd like.~
@46 = ~Ahhh, just lookin' at these boots reminds me of gazin' at the skies over the harbor at night.~
@47 = ~If'n ye want me to improve Crommus' old boots for ye, I'd need a few things.  Two potions each of magic protection, magic shielding, and magic blocking.~
@48 = ~Ye have all the potions I need here to reforge those starry boots, I would just need 5,000gp for me work at the forge.  Shall I get started on em for ye?~
@49 = ~Placeholder~
@50 = ~Ahh, I believe I recognize the craftmanship of this Green Dragonscale o' yers.  Jegg's works is it?  How is the ol' bird?~
@51 = ~I can rework this dragonscale into better armor if ye can bring me some red or shadow dragon scales.~
@52 = ~Aye, ye've collected some more scales from the dastardly beasts.  I can use 'em to reforge yer green dragonscale.~
@52 = ~I can use these dragon scales to reforge your green dragonscale armor.~
@53 = ~I can use these red dragon scales to reforge the green dragonscale into sturdy plate.~
@54 = ~What've ye here, scales from a noxious green dragon?~
@55 = ~I can use these scales to make for ye a suit of armor, or a sturdy shield.~
@56 = ~It'll cost ye 7,500gp and a day's worth of yer sweat helping at me forge.~
@57 = ~I can use these shadow dragon scales to reforge the green dragonscale into a lightweight scale armor.~
@58 = ~Scales from a shadow dragon?  I can use these to further enhance your armor.~
@59 = ~This be a nice greatsword ye have here, a dragon's gift?  She looks rather worn...~
@60 = ~I can use either these red dragon scales or shadow dragon scales to reforge your green dragonscale.~
@61 = ~It'll cost ye 15,000 gold and since me apprentice would rather chase harlots and courtesans than work, ye'll need to stay on a day and help me run the forge.~
@62 = ~Well, let's see what ye got then.~
@63 = ~I can reforge this blade, I would just need a sharp new blade for the forgin'.  A Githyanki's vorpal blade of silver would work best.~
@64 = ~Ahh yes, this be a vorpal blade alright, I can use it to reforge that dragon's sword of yours, along with 7,500 gold for me trouble.~
@65 = ~The Verdant Crimson Dragon Plate?  Ye wish to improve it further, eh?~
@66 = ~I can rework the armor for ye with some more scales.  Blue, white, shadow, green, or silver will do.~
@67 = ~Scales from a shadow dragon?  I can use these to further enhance your armor.~
@68 = ~Ye would like to enhance that silver dragon's blade of yers further, ye say?~
@69 = ~Scales from a white dragon? I can use these to further enhance your armor.~
@70 = ~Scales from a dragon of noble silver?  It saddens this old dwarf to know such a creature fell for these scales.  However, we shouldn't let them go to waste.  I can use these to improve your armor.~
@71 = ~Enhancing a vorpal blade be a tall order, I'd need an elemental gemstone for it, and 10,000gp to fit it to your sword.~
@72 = ~Scales from a blue dragon?  I can use these to enhance your armor.~
@73 = ~Looks like ye have an elemental gem of frost here, I can use this to enhance your dragon blade with.~
@74 = ~It'll cost ye 20,000 gold, and since me apprentice has ran off to Waterdeep with a rather homely courtesan, I'll need yer help at the forge once again.~
@75 = ~I can use these dragon scales to enhance your dragonscale armor with.~
@76 = ~Fancy yerself a dragonslayer, do ye?  I can use any of these scales to enhance your dragonscale armor with.~
@77 = ~The Verdant Shadow Dragonscale?  Ye wish to improve it further, eh?~
@78 = ~I can rework the armor for ye with some more scales.  Blue, white, red, or silver will do.~
@79 = ~Scales from a red dragon?  I can use these to further enhance your armor.~
@80 = ~Well now, I haven't seen any of these in an age... be these a pair of stalker's gauntlets?~
@81 = ~Always wanted to try me hand at reforgin a pair o' these, and I believe I can do it for ye with a bracers of blinding strike, an improved haste scroll, two potions of power and two potions of master thievery.~
@82 = ~Ye have everything I need here to upgrade those stalker gauntlets of yers.  It'll be 10,000gp and I'll need yer help at me forge.  Me son of a kobald of an apprentice was out all hours deep in his cups with the blasted courtesans again.~
@83 = ~The Scorched Earth again eh?  Not hot enough for ye?  Heh.~
@84 = ~Be a difficult task to make this blade burn hotter... but I might just be able to do it for ye if'n ye can find me an elemental gem of flame.  Oh, and a small comission for me work, 15,000gp should cover it.  And lest I forget, I'll need yer help for the day at me forge.  That damnable apprentice of mine has gone and knocked up a half-orc lass.  I doubt I will ever see him again, heh.~
@85 = ~Looks like ye found an elemental gem of flame, they be rare as hen's teeth.  Shall we get started on mounting it into yer blade?~
@86 = ~What've ye got here?  A lucky belt ye say?~
@87 = ~Methinks I can make this belt even more "lucky" for ye and yer friends with five scrolls of luck and 10,000gp.~
@88 = ~Ye have everything I need to fix up that lucky belt for ye, I'll just need yer help at the forge again.  That half orc lass did a real number on me apprentice, he's going to be laid up a few days at least, the scoundrel.  Shall we begin?~
@89 = ~Now this is an odd bird, a cursed staff that's uncursed...but still cursed?~
@90 = ~I may just be able to empower that accursed stick o' yers a bit.  I would need a wand of fire, a wand of frost, and 5,000gp.~
@91 = ~Aye, ye got the wands I need here for the uncursed staff.  Would ye like me to do the work?  As much as I hate ta ask, I'll need yer help again.   My apprentice be at the temple with the half-orc lass, she be makin' an honest man o' him whether he want it or not, ha!~
@92 = ~Ahh, yer accursed stick again, ye would like to have it recharged ye say?~
@93 = ~Ol' Cromwell might be able to work some more magic into that old stick with another wand of fire, a wand of frost, and another 5,000gp for me trouble.~
@94 = ~Ye have another wand of fire and frost here too, shall we get to work?  Me apprentice is away on his honeymoon with the half-orc lass at the Low Lantern in Baldur's Gate, I'll need ye to help me again.~
@95 = ~Ahh, ye've got an old backwhacker here, I could use one of these for me bastard apprentice.  Just to keep 'im in line o' course.~
@96 = ~If'n ye come accross a wyvern tail and a gnasher club, I can reforge this backwhacker into a really nasty implement for a rogue.  I'd just need a mere 5,000gp for me trouble.~
@97 = ~Ye've got the wyvern tail and gnasher.  Ye ready to get started on the whacker?  Just one day's worth of yer help at me forge again if'n ye can.  Me apprentice is nursing a hangover he says, Pfft.~
@98 = ~Hmm, be this bow of orcish origin?  Looks to be quite frightening.~
@99 = ~I can make this banshee's bow wail upon your enemies for you, I would just need something like some screaming bagpipes to make it do so, along with a bowstring of gesen or gond to hold it all together.~
@100 = ~I would need 10,000gp and yer help fer the day.  Me apprentice managed to smash his hand with me anvil and will be laid up fer awhile.~
@101 = ~I can use this Githyanki hilt to reforge that devil's sword if ye would like, it would cost ye 10,000 gold fer the work.~
@102 = ~I can use Angurvadal and the scroll to reforge that devil's sword if ye would like, just a mere pittance of 10,000 gold for tha' forgin.~
@103 = ~Hmm, looks like ye have the hilt, and the blazing sword and scroll too, I could use either to reforge that devil's blade if ye would like.  Just toss me 10,000 gold for me coffers and I'll get started~
@104 = ~It doesn't look like ye have what I need to reforge that hellblade...~
@105 = ~Let's see if ye got all I need to rework this orcish bow...~ 
@106 = ~I can use this gesen bowstring along with yer bagpipes to improve your bow.~
@107 = ~I can use this bowstring of gond along with yer bagpipes to improve your bow.~
@108 = ~Quite the adventurer you must be to have bowstrings from gond and gesen.~
@109 = ~Ye have some of the parts here, but I'll need the screaming pipes along with one of the gond or gesen bowstrings to complete the work.~
@110 = ~I'd need 10,000gp and yer help fer the day at me forge.~
@111 = ~Nice gloves ye got here, just in me size too!~
@112 = ~I can reforge these gloves for ye and make them a better fit too with some extra materials. Mayhap some bracers of archery, a bracers of defense AC3, some gloves of pickpocketing and 5,000gp for the stitchwork.~
@113 = ~Looks like ye got all the materials I need to reforge yer doeskin gloves, Ye up for another day o' work with me at me shop?~
@114 = ~What've ye here....a blackened arrow that seems to sap the strength right from me arm...~
@115 = ~I can make ye more of these arrows, mayhap even an unlimited supply with the right components.  I would just need on of yer arrows, a quiver of plenty +2 and 5,000 gold.~
@116 = ~I can use this quiver of plenty +2 to make an unlimited supply of these darkness arrows for ye, I just need 5,000 gold and yer help at me forge for the day.~
@117 = ~What've ye here....a blackened bullet that seems to sap the strength right from me arm...~
@118 = ~I can make ye more of these bullets, mayhap even an unlimited supply with the right components.  I would just need one of yer bullets, a bag of plenty +2 and 5,000 gold.~
@119 = ~I can use this bag of plenty +2 to make an unlimited supply of these darkness bullets for ye, I just need 5,000 gold and yer help at me forge for the day.~
@120 = ~Ahh, this be a rather nice old wizard's cloak ye got here.~
@121 = ~I can reforge this cloak for ye into something really special for the aracnially-inclined, I'll just need an amulet of metaspell influence to make a new clasp, and a cloak of displacement for a new lining.  I'll also need yer help fer the day at me forge.~
@122 = ~Ye have the cloak I need fer the lining, and the metaspell amulet for a new clasp.  5,000gp and we can get started.~
@123 = ~Hmmm, very nice dagger ye got here, imbued with all the elements at once?~
@124 = ~Ye know, this dagger o' yers would be much more useful if'n ye could throw it.  I could improve it as such with a boomerang dagger and 5,000gp fer the forgin'.~
@125 = ~Ye have a boomerang dagger here, I can use it to enhance that elemental dagger.  Me apprentice didn't show up again today, so I will need yer help fer the day.~
@126 = ~Ah, the elemental dagger again, ye want it further enhanced?~
@127 = ~Enhancing this elemental dagger is a tall order, ye would need to find me an elemental gem to use with it.~
@128 = ~I can use the Soul of Frost to enhance yer elemental dagger, I just need 5,000gp and yer help at the forge.~
@129 = ~Ach!  Ye should warn a dwarf before ye hand him a blasted pike that shocks ye!~
@130 = ~I could reforge the storm pike if'n ye find me a wave shaft to work with.~
@131 = ~Aye, this be the haft of the bitch-queens' weapon.  I can use it to reforge the storm pike into a throwing axe or a halberd for ye.~
@132 = ~I would need the wave shaft and 7,500gp.  Oh, and lest I forget, I'll need yer help at the forge again, me apprentice was found dead in the sewers with a courtesan's heel stuck in his back.~
@133 = ~The maelstrom axe?  Aye, I can enhance it further for ye.~
@134 = ~I would need the hammer of thunderbolts +3 along with the scroll of crom faeyr, and 10,000gp for me work to enhance the maelstrom axe.~
@135 = ~Ye have the hammer of thunderbolts and the scroll, I can reforge yer axe with these.~
@136 = ~The maelstrom pike?  Aye, I can enhance it further for ye.~
@137 = ~I would need the wave blade, and the scroll of crom faeyr, and 10,000gp for me work to enhance the maelstrom pike?~
@138 = ~Ye have the wave blade and the scroll, I can reforge the pike with these.~
@139 = ~Aye, what's this?  An ioun stone of magiked troll's blood?  Smells worse than me apprentice after a night at the tavern with well-loved harlots.~
@140 = ~I could reforge this inoun stone for ye, it needs a warrior's spirit to focus the power inside.  If'n ye can somehow find a pale green ioun stone in yer travels, I could use it, along with five scrolls of resist fear, and five potions of regeneration, and five potions of heroism to enhance yer ioun stone.~
@141 = ~This be the pale green stone I need, the potions and the scrolls.  Toss in 5,000gp for me coffers and I'll get to work for ye.~
@142 = ~Ye want me to further enhance the trollkiller ioun stone?~
@143 = ~It be a tall order to enhance the trollkiller stone further, I'd need another green ioun stone with a warrior's fighting spirit, and another 5,000gp for the forgin'.~
@144 = ~This be a green stone with another fighter's spirit inside alright.  Shall we get started on using it to enahnce yer trollkiller stone?~
@145 = ~A shield from the Egons?  Looks like it's seen better days, friend.~
@146 = ~Cromwell can reforge it for ye, I would need another shield to rework it with, such as a shield of the lost +2, and would need some illithium ore for the finish.~
@147 = ~Aye, I can work with this ore and shield.  7,500gp for the commission and I can get started right away for ye.~
@148 = ~What've ye brought for me today?  Looks to be a shortblade with some rather sharp scales for an edge.~
@149 = ~To further improve this blade for ye, I would need a heart of the damned and 7,500gp.~
@150 = ~Ye have the heart here, and the gold, I'll just need yer help at me forge again for the day, me apprentice took one hell of a beatin from a sailor at the tavern last eve.~
@151 = ~Ahh, the bulwark of egons, ye wish it improved further ye say?~
@152 = ~I can improve yer shield with an old symbol of the sun god, Amaunator, if ye find one, bring it back here and I'll fix up yer shield for a meager 5,000gp.~
@153 = ~The symbol of Amaunator!  I can use this to improve yer bulwark of egons.  Shall we get to work on 'er?~
@154 = ~This be one heavenly crossbow ye got here, ye wish it enhanced eh?~
@155 = ~I could enhance this bow for ye, I would need something to make a new limb with, say a gesen bowshaft.  And I would need 5,000 fer me trouble.~
@156 = ~This be gesen's work alright, I can use this to enhance yer crossbow.~
@157 = ~Interesting find ye have here, an ethereal spear of sorts?~
@158 = ~I could reforge this shadowed spear of yers into something special, I would need ye to bring me an elemental gem.~
@159 = ~I'll be... an elemental gem of wind, I can use this to enhance that shadowy spear of yers.  I just need 7,500gp and yer help at me forge.~
@160 = ~Ye want the Shadowed Spear of the Tempest enhanced further ye say?~
@161 = ~I could do the reforgin, I'd need a new head for the spear.  Ixil's spike would do the trick if'n ye can find it.~
@162 = ~Ye have Ixil's spike here, I can use this to reforge yer spear.  I would need another 7,500gp and a day at the forge.~
@163 = ~Scales from a green dragon?  I can use these to further enhance your armor.~
@164 = ~Ye say ye would like yer dragonscale shield made sturdier?~
@165 = ~Hmmm, it would take some extremely tough scales to improve this shield, only some from a black dragon would work.~
@166 = ~Ye certainly are a brave one to have slain a black dragon for these scales.  I can use these to enhance yer shield.  I would need 7,500gp fer the commission, shall we begin work?~
@167 = ~Ye would like to improve the Tongue of Acid even further?~
@168 = ~It be a tall order to improve that hellblade more, I'd need to reforge it using an elemental gemstone and it would take 15,000gp fer my work at the forge.~
@169 = ~By the Soul Forger, an elemental gem of corrosive ichor?  Never thought I'd see such a thing in me lifetime.  I can use this to reforge yer hellblade.  I would just need 15,000gp and yer help at me forge again.~
@170 = ~Ey, whats this?  Appears to be Iriaeborian craftsmanship that forged this armor.~
@171 = ~I could greatly improve the protective ability of this shadowy armor if ye can bring me some scales from a black dragon.~
@172 = ~Ye've gone and slain a black dragon 'ave ye?  These scales will do nicely for your Iriaeborian leathers.   Just a toss 7,500gp in fer me coffers and I'll get to work for ye.~
@173 = ~Ey?  What be this?  Some accursed bard's bracers?~
@174 = ~Hmmm, ye know, ol' Cromwell may be able to make these jokers' bracers better for ye.  It'd take some dark magic though.  I'd need to use the power from two demon's hearts along with 5,000gp fer me trouble, and I cannae gaurantee the curse would be lifted.~
@175 = ~Well now, ye've gone and carved two hearts from demons.  I'll not ask ye where from, but if'n ye would like me to use em to enhance those bracers of yers, I'll get to work right away.~
@176 = ~Ye have a blessed ring here, do ye?  Did ye pluck this one from Strohm's tomb?  I cannae hardly believe me eyes.~
@177 = ~I can improve this holy ring fer ya with an equally holy gemstone, such as the Eye of Tyr.~
@178 = ~Ah, yes indeed, this be the Eye of Tyr, I can use this to improve the ring of purity.  I just need 5,000gp and a day at the forge for the work.~
@179 = ~A Calimshite saber?  Nicely balanced and quick, ye would like it improved?~
@180 = ~I can reforge this blade if ye can bring me another fast saber, like the Belm +2, and a murky oil of speed to temper it with.~
@181 = ~Ye have the Belm +2 and the oil I need to reforge this blade for you, just 5,000gp fer me work and it's a done deal.~
@182 = ~Hmm, very interesting blade ye have here, quite cold to the touch, and seething with anger.  This be one of the old Sharran blades ye say?~
@183 = ~Aye, I can enhance this blade for ye, it needs something to balance and focus the raw anger from the spirit trapped within.  I'd need either the blade or hilt from the ancient sword, Equalizer, if'n ye can find them.~
@184 = ~Let me rummage through yer pack and see if ye have something I can use to enhance this dark blade for ye...~
@185 = ~Ah, ye've gone and found the blade of the Equalizer, I can use this to enhance that dead priestess' blade of yours.~
@186 = ~Ah, ye've gone and found the hilt of the Equalizer, I can use this to enhance that dead priestess' blade of yours.~
@187 = ~Quite the treasure hunter ye be, having located both the hilt and blade of the Equalizer.  I can use either to enhance Varscona for ye.~
@188 = ~I would just need the hilt and 5,000gp for the commission to do the work.~
@189 = ~I would just need the blade and 5,000gp for the commission to do the work.~
@190 = ~The Varscona +3?  Ye would like it further enhanced?  Quite a feat to enhance this blade further methinks...~
@191 = ~Aye, I can enhance the dark blade further, but I would need an elemental gemstone of frost to do so.~
@192 = ~Ye have the Soul of Frost here, I can use this to reforge Varscona +3 into a far more powerful blade, I would just need 10,000gp for the work and yer help for the day once again at me forge.~
@193 = ~It cannae be.... a magical axe from the lost Stonfire clan!  It was here in Athkatla in some blasted tavern, ye say?~
@194 = ~It'd be a right honor to enhance this fine piece o' dwarven craftsmanship for ye.  To do so would take nothing less than an elemental gemstone of flame and 10,000 gold crowns.~
@195 = ~Aye, this is certainly a gemstone of flame ye have here, shall we get to work on yer axe?~
@196 = ~Ah, this looks to be some scrappy ol' wizard's hat...~
@197 = ~If'n ye would like to have this old hat enhanced, it'd take some potent magics.  Methinks it would take the Circlet of Netheril, nothing less.~
@198 = ~Aye, this be the Cirlet of Netheril ye have here.  I can enhance that old pointy hat of yers with it along with a mere 10,000 gold crowns fer me trouble at tha' forge~
@199 = ~The Sourceror's Cap?  Ye say ye would like it enhanced further?  Hmmm, let me think a moment...~
