Damage Type: Slashing
Speed Factor: 2
Proficiency Type: Long Sword
Type: One-handed
Requires:
 6 Strength

Weight: 2~
@2005 = ~Tongue of Burning Acid +5~
@2006 = ~After setting the Eye of Ichor into the pommel, this infernal blade from Avernus has reached its full potential.  Ghastly green caustic flames roar from the tongue-like blade of the sword, inflicting agonzing, crippling pain on its victims, slowing their ability to fight.  In addition, the weilder may blanket <PRO_HISHER> foes in a cuastic fog, causing acid damage and asphyxiating them.   Eerily, the inscription on the hilt seems to have changed on its own: "cuts sharper than any scream, burns hotter than any rage", giving the uneasy feeling that the blade itself is rather pleased with its horrific endowment.

STATISTICS:

Equipped Abilities:
– Negative Plane Protection

Charge Abilities:
– Caustic Fog once per day
  Damage: 2d4 (acid) per round (No Save)
  Special: Movement rate slowed by 50% for one round (No Save) Chance per round of -2 penalty to dexterity, -2 penalty to strength, and unconcious for one round (Save vs. Spell at -2 negates)
  Special: No effect on unbreathing creatures
  Range: 40 ft.
  Area of Effect: 12-ft. radius
