@2237 = ~The Forger +3~
@2238 = ~This is Cromwell's personal hammer, a gift given to him by a rogue djinn attempting to escape from her indentured servitude at the hands of a very cruel Vizier whom abused her at his every whim and forced her to perform heinous deeds against innocents for his own amusement and gain.  After arriving in Athkatla, the djinn quickly fled from her docked ship into the first domicile she could find,  which happened to be Cromwell's shop.  After explaining her situation and pleading for help, Cromwell agreed to perform a dangerous and rare enchantment on the djinn's lamp to reverse the relationship between master and servant.  Once he caught up to her, the enfuriated Vizier immediately used his powerful magics to wrest the lamp from the djinn.  In his haste, he immediately rubbed the lamp to trap the djinn.  Much to his dismay, he was drawn into the lamp against his will, imprisoning himself and freeing the djinn.  The grateful djinn gifted this hammer to Cromwell before returning to Calimshan.  Over the years, Cromwell has used this hammer to forge many powerful magic items, and its power has grown as magics continue to seep slowly into it from his works.  None know what happend to the accursed lamp containing the eil Vizier, but it is said to be somewhere at the bottom of the trackless sea.

